New TV / Sports oriented bar meets Old World Neighborhood. This is a gem in the neighborhood.  Great Location.  Great view of all the bright TVs.  Mini patio on the sidewalk.  Windows open weather permitting for street vibe (and fresh air).  The room is square vs long and thin, which I liked as it provides an open feel and more room between guests.  The interior is decorated well and has warmer feel.  Ceiling and a the bar foot rest are patterned.   The light bulbs cast a warm orange glow.  The interior appeared well kept in the dining and bathroom.  Staff was available for another round without being intrusive at our visit.  Food is middling decent.  It's no a gastro-pub.  It's a straight up menu, uncomplicated.  Beer list is middle of the road craft beer.  I think a gap might be a craft dart (like an oatmeal or coffee stout).  Recommended for a casual place on the NW side. Recommended for sports.  Check with bar on games available.

This is a cool fresh spot in the neighborhood and I was excited to try it out. My wife and I came through on a Sunday evening to find it pretty quiet around dinner--seems the customer base is still growing. The atmosphere is very nice here, it has an excellent look and feel, and is itself a highlight of the place. The beer selection is quite good, and the menu about what you'd expect, with an average selection of pub goodies with some very present influcne of Mexican cuisine. I got the Boss Hog (pictured), which I found to be pretty good, but a bit indulgent. Carnitas, bacon, and ham--frankly, I'd dump the bacon at least, as that just got in the way and distracted from genuinely good carnitas and various toppings. No need to add greasy, attention grabbing bacon to that. A small refinement could go a long way! Anyways--i enjoyed the pickle on the side, the tater tots were great, and service was friendly and at ease. Will be back!

This place has so much potential but is currently failing to live up to it. The facilities are beautiful and it creates a great aesthetic, very warm and inviting. The wait staff is very friendly but seems poorly trained, both times that I've been in and asked simple  questions, they had to go ask someone for help.  The bar selection is great for beer and cocktails but the wine is awful. It's evident they're trying to stretch out bottles of red by refrigerating them which only makes cold, bad wine. Finally, the food is awful. The burger came out with a grayish hue, the nachos were a soggy mess, and the fried chicken sandwich was something you'd see in a highschool cafeteria.  I really hope they can make some changes and improve things here as the location is excellent. I would love to bring people here regularly but the shortcomings of Crawford's are really holding it back.
